com.sap.cloud.sdk.cloudplatform.connectivity

Class ScpCfHttpDestination

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.cloud.sdk.cloudplatform.connectivity.AbstractScpDestination
      • com.sap.cloud.sdk.cloudplatform.connectivity.ScpCfHttpDestination
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DestinationProperties, HttpDestination, HttpDestinationProperties

    public class ScpCfHttpDestination
extends AbstractScpDestination
implements HttpDestination
    SCP Cloud Foundry specific representation of a HTTP destination as a collection of key-value pairs.

    Additionally provides a builder to construct instances.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ScpCfHttpDestination

        protected ScpCfHttpDestination(@Nonnull
                               DestinationProperties baseDestination)
        Create an instance by wrapping an existing DestinationProperties object. To be representable as a ScpCfHttpDestination, the existing destination object must have the following:
        • DestinationProperty.NAME property set.
        • DestinationProperty.TYPE property set to DestinationType.HTTP.
        • DestinationProperty.URI property set to a valid URL.
        Parameters:
        baseDestination - Existing destination object that implements the DestinationProperties interface.

      • ScpCfHttpDestination

        protected ScpCfHttpDestination(@Nonnull
                               HttpDestinationProperties baseDestination)
        Create an instance by wrapping an existing HttpDestinationProperties object. To be representable as a ScpCfHttpDestination, the existing destination object must have the following:
        • DestinationProperty.NAME property set.
        • DestinationProperty.TYPE property set to DestinationType.HTTP.
        • DestinationProperty.URI property set to a valid URL.
        Parameters:
        baseDestination - Existing destination object that implements the HttpDestinationProperties interface.
